The state of the kimchi backend looks like this: where Field: PrimeField,
{ /// A counter used to track variables /// (similar to the one in the snarky wrapper) next_internal_var: usize, /// Instruction on how to compute each internal variable /// (as a linear combination of other variables). /// Used during witness generation. internal_vars: HashMap<InternalVar, (Vec<(Field, V)>, Option<Field>)>, /// The symbolic execution trace table. /// Each cell is a variable that takes a value during witness generation. /// (if not set, it will take the value 0). rows: Vec<Vec<Option<V>>>, /// The circuit once compiled gates: Circuit<Field>, /// The row to use the next time we add a constraint. // TODO: I think we can delete this next_row: usize, /// The size of the public input /// (which fills the first rows of our constraint system. public_input_size: Option<usize>, // omitted values...
}
